            <fr:title text="negatively univalent deductive system">negatively univalent deductive system</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0048.xml" title="deductive system" addr="jms-0048" type="local">deductive system</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is called <html:em>negatively univalent</html:em> when for any negative <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\in \mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>, the type of negative objects <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\in \mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004R.xml" title="thunkably and linearly invertible maps" addr="jms-004R" type="local">linearly invertible</fr:link> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004A.xml" title="linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">linear</fr:link> map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:B\vdash  A]]></fr:tex> is contractible.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>4</fr:month>
              <fr:day>15</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-004M</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004M.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="upshift structure">upshift structure</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0048.xml" title="deductive system" addr="jms-0048" type="local">deductive system</fr:link> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be an object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>. An <html:em>upshift structure</html:em> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a
  <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004B.xml" title="positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">negative</fr:link> object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathord {\Uparrow } A]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004A.xml" title="linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">linear</fr:link> map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {force}_{A} : \mathord {\Uparrow } A\vdash  A]]></fr:tex> for which there exists a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004N.xml" title="linear and thunkable inverses" addr="jms-004N" type="local">necessarily unique and thunkable</fr:link> inverse <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {delay}_{A} : A\vdash  \mathord {\Uparrow } A]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
